Scope of this fork
------------------

claude-hud renders the Claude Code statusline using the rate-limit fields
that Anthropic's API returns inside Claude Code's stdin payload. Users
routing Claude Code to Kimi (ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.kimi.com/coding)
do not receive those fields, so the upstream "Usage" / "Weekly" bars never
render for them.

This fork adds a new data source that calls Kimi's `/v1/usages` endpoint
directly and feeds the same `UsageData` shape into the existing renderer,
producing accurate 5-hour and 7-day quota bars for Kimi users.

Files modified or added by this fork:

  - src/kimi-api.ts           (new) — Kimi /v1/usages fetch + cache
  - src/index.ts              (modified) — wire Kimi into the usage chain
  - .claude-plugin/*.json     (modified) — plugin / marketplace metadata
  - package.json              (modified) — package name + description
  - README.md, README.zh.md   (rewritten)
  - LICENSE                   (added fork copyright line)
  - NOTICE                    (new)

All other source files, including the entire `src/render/` tree and
`src/types.ts`, are unchanged from upstream claude-hud and continue to
operate under upstream's MIT terms.
